{"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"ImageDataPicker-Hero"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The ImageDataPicker framework provides a simple control to select photos using SwiftUI’s PhotosPicker and then store the selected image to a SwiftData Model. The control presents a thumbnail view of the selected image that can be clipped to various geometries (round, square or rounded). A customisable placeholder image is presented if no image has been selected or an error loading the image occurs."}]},{"text":"How to use the ImageDataPicker Framework","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"How-to-use-the-ImageDataPicker-Framework"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"ImageDataPicker-Header","type":"image"}]},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You start by adding the ImageDataPicker Framework (ImageDataPicker.xcframework) to your Xcode project.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Create a SwiftData Model to store your image or an @State variable to hold the image data. The model should have a ","type":"text"},{"code":"Data","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" attribute that can be bound directly to the ImageDataPicker.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.technistic.ImageDataPicker\/documentation\/ImageDataPicker\/ImageDataPickerView","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" to your View and bind it to your imageData."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can use the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.technistic.ImageDataPicker\/documentation\/ImageDataPicker\/SquareImageViewModifier","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" view modifier to clip the image to a specific shape,